    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nYou're building a program to remind people of small actions they can take each day to reduce their carbon footprint. You already have two functions: one reminds them to turn off unused lights, and the other encourages using reusable water bottles. Now you'll create a function that combines both reminders into a single daily message.\r\n\r\n1. Read the two functions: `turn_off_lights()` and `use_reusable_bottle()`.\r\n\r\n2. Write a new function called `daily_reminder()` that **calls both of the existing functions in order**.\r\n\r\n3. After you define `daily_reminder()`, call it to show your final message.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nFunctions can call other functions—just make sure the ones you're calling are defined first!",
